| **Day 1 Download** | **Day 1 First plan** | **Day 3–7 Building trust** | **Day 14 Habit formed** | **Day 30 Retained** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Hears about Foofoo from housing society WhatsApp group. Downloads. Completes onboarding in 4 minutes. | Opens app. Sees first day's meal plan — feels regional (Poha, Dal Bati style for MP origin). Surprised it isn't generic North Indian. | Uses app daily. Swipes a few meals she doesn't want. Locks breakfast slot (Poha every weekday). Never-lists baingan — hates it. | Opens app before getting out of bed. Shares a meal plan screenshot to housing society WhatsApp: 'This app is amazing.' | Cannot imagine meal planning without Foofoo. Notices Premium features (meal insights, family analytics). Considers upgrading. |
| *Curious but sceptical. Has tried recipe apps before.* | *Intrigued. **'**How does it know I like these?**'* | *Building habit. Checking app before deciding what to cook.* | *Loyal. Evangelist. Refers 3 neighbours.* | *Dependent in a good way. Sees value in Premium.* |
